@node Empty Trash

                                 EMPTY TRASH
                                 -----------
The Trashcan is just another way of @{" Deleting " link delete} files.
The bonus of using the @{" Trashcan " link using the trashcan} is that files are not 
deleted immediately, they are stored ready for deletion by you later. 

If you 'Empty Trash' then any files you have previously @{" dragged " link mouse} to the 
Trash Can for deletion will now be deleted proper, you will NOT be able
to retrieve any files after this operation.

Please view this @{" Diagram " system " showpic trash.iff"}

QUICK GUIDE IN PLAIN ENGLISH
----------------------------
* Make sure the disk in use is not @{" write protected "link write}.
* Move the mouse pointer to the ICONS @{" menu " link menu} at the top of the screen.
* @{" Highlight " link highlight} EMPTY TRASH and then release the right mouse button.
* All files in the Trashcan will now be deleted.


FURTHER INFORMATION
-------------------
You can make a Trashcan on your disk by choosing the "Trashcan" option
when you @{ " Format " link Format} a disk.
@{" Icons " link icon} can only be moved to a Trashcan of the same volume.
You cannot delete whole disks from the Trashcan
The Trashcan itself cannot be moved into a drawer.

@endnode

@node Delete

                                    DELETE
                                    ------
Delete performs the exact operation you would expect, it deletes files.
All you need to do is @{" highlight " link highlight} an @{" icon " link icon} and then select "Delete" from
the Icons @{" menu " link menu}.

Take a look at this @{" diagram " system " showpic delete.iff"}

*WARNING* Once you have deleted a file you will not be able to retrieve it
          without the help of a @{" Public Domain " link pd} program, I recommend 
          Arestaure as the easiest and best to use.


QUICK GUIDE IN PLAIN ENGLISH
----------------------------
* Make sure the disk in use is not @{" write protected " link write}.
* Locate the desired icon to be deleted.
* @{" Click "link mouse} once on the icon with the left mouse button.
* Move the mouse pointer to the ICONS menu at the top of the screen.
* Highlight DELETE and then release the right mouse button.
* Click on Ok to the requester to continue the deletion
* Or click on cancel to abort the operation.

FURTHER INFORMATION
-------------------
You cannot DELETE a disk icon as such, use @{" Format " link Format}

@endnode



